Congressman Donald Payne, Chairman of the Congressional Black Caucus Foundation and former Chairman of the Congressional Black Caucus, has passed away. President Obama expressed his sadness and acknowledged Payne's significant contributions throughout his life. Payne served as the first African American President of the National Council of YMCAs and later became the first African American Congressman to represent New Jersey. He dedicated himself to fighting for working families, advocating for issues such as increasing the minimum wage, ensuring worker safety, providing affordable healthcare, and improving the educational system. Payne was also a leader in US-Africa policy, actively working to restore democracy and human rights on the continent. The President offered condolences to Payne's family and friends during this challenging time.